I think this should be the `"sub"` in the JWT token or the username in the `Basic` authorization value, or `cfg::Auth.user` won't work if it's set to non-`edgedb` values. But that's probably an acceptable unimplemented feature at this moment, because this endpoint wasn't protected at all.

@author:
`sub` isn't always present in the JWTs we generate, though. Ones for local instances have no `sub` but do have `"edgedb.server.any_role"` set.

Our cloud tokens do have a `sub` set, and it seems to be a random alphanumeric string; does it actually correspond to a role in edgedb?

@user2:
`sub` in the cloud token is the id of the cloud user, no relation to role, as those are specified in token scope instead.  We have the `X-EdgeDB-User` header to communicate the desired role instead.  Default to `edgedb` if it isn't present I guess.

